Step Brothers 2 Filming in Buckeye, Arizona, Plot Details Released – WM21 News
HOLLYWOOD, California – The 2008 Will Ferrell comedy, Step Brothers, is finally getting a sequel and will film in Buckeye, Arizona next summer. Reports are claiming that all of the original cast will return including Will Ferrell, John C. Reilly, Adam Scott, Mary Steenburgen, Richard Jenkins, and others.

The producers released a short description of the upcoming film but refused to provide any details beyond that: The two step brothers have moved to Buckeye, Arizona where they live together and also work together at the same menial job. Dale finds out that he’s somehow impregnated his “girlfriend” but when the young woman leaves the new baby with Dale and Brennan the two are left to raise the child themselves.

A casting call for extras from the Buckeye area is set to begin later this year. Let us know what you think about the new Step Brothers sequel in the comments section below and don’t forget to click the share button to share with friends.

